news.title: Uttar Pradesh government sanctions ₹736 crore for PMAY urban housing
news.para: The Uttar Pradesh government has approved the budget for Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana. This is for the financial year 2025-26. A fund of Rs 736 crore is allocated. The aim is to provide housing for urban poor families across the state. The central and state governments jointly run the scheme. Eligible families receive grants and subsidies.

news.title: Rudrapur: Registry ban remains on 790 illegal colonies in Udham Singh Nagar
news.para: Udham Singh Nagar administration continues its ban on property registrations in 790 illegally developed colonies identified in May. A detailed report suggesting solutions has been sent to the state government. The crackdown revealed misuse of agricultural land, with many colonies backed by influential figures, awaiting further directives from the state government.

news.title: Jaipur: JMC-H demolishes two rickety buildings, seals one in Walled City
news.para: Jaipur Municipal Corporation Heritage initiated a demolition drive, razing two unsafe buildings in the Walled City's Johari Bazaar, while also providing temporary housing for affected residents. Simultaneously, the JMC-H mayor led a plantation drive, adding 201 Champa saplings to the Kishanpole market's green belt. Furthermore, a 'Swachhata Ki Paathshala' was organized to educate students on cleanliness and waste management.

news.title: Panchkula's Gandhi Colony faces bulldozers before Navratras
news.para: Authorities are preparing to clear Gandhi Colony, a slum settlement near Mata Mansa Devi Mandir, before Navratras. A recent survey revealed around 1,000 illegal structures on encroached land, prompting concerns among residents facing potential eviction.

news.title: Prayagraj civic body to charge fixed fees for property name transfer
news.para: Prayagraj Municipal Corporation approved a new sub-rule significantly reducing property name transfer fees, benefiting many citizens. Fixed fees based on property value slabs will replace the current percentage-based system, potentially saving middle-class families substantial amounts. The PMC will seek public input before final implementation, also addressing delayed streetlight repairs ahead of upcoming festivals.

news.title: Hyderabad business duo buys Delhi bungalow for ₹140 crore
news.para: Sasidhar Chinta and Lakshmi Priyadarshini Chinta of Vishwa Samudra Group acquired a sprawling 883-square metre bungalow in Delhi's Jor Bagh for ₹140 crore, with the sale registered in June. This transaction highlights the enduring demand for high-value properties in the prestigious Lutyens' Bungalow Zone, known for its exclusive residences and central location.

news.title: NeoLiv enters agreement to develop land in Khopoli
news.para: NeoLiv, founded by Mohit Malhotra, is set to develop a 47-acre mixed-use community in Khopoli, Maharashtra, with a gross development value of approximately Rs 600 crore. This project, backed by UHNI investors and a SEBI-regulated AIF fund, aims to capitalize on the growing real estate hub driven by infrastructure developments.

news.title: Tenant verification neglected in Ranchi: Police urge landlords to comply
news.para: Tenant verification in Ranchi remains neglected, raising safety concerns after recent criminal incidents. Despite directives from the city SP to collect tenant details, many police stations admit to minimal or no verifications. Police cite landlord negligence in reporting new tenants, allowing criminals to exploit rental accommodations.

news.title: Chandigarh administrator takes ‘laggard’ CHB to task
news.para: Punjab Governor Gulab Chand Kataria criticized the Chandigarh Housing Board for its failure to provide affordable housing. The board hasn't launched a new project in almost ten years. He reviewed the board's performance and expressed concern over staffing and rental dues. The governor directed officials to finalize the Sector 53 housing project and launch it before Diwali.

news.title: Chandigarh administration notifies increase in property conversion charges
news.para: Chandigarh property owners face significantly higher conversion charges for leasehold to freehold properties, as the administration has increased rates by two to four times, linking them directly to the revised collector rates. This revision, the first since 2017, means conversion charges will automatically adjust with future collector rate changes.

news.title: No new rooftop construction atop residential buildings: West Bengal government
news.para: The urban development department in West Bengal has prohibited new rooftop construction on residential buildings, mandating the restoration of existing rooftop establishments for common residential use. Commercial rooftop establishments in non-residential buildings can continue if they occupy only half the space for emergency refuge.

news.title: Karnataka-RERA ruling brings hope for distressed plot owners
news.para: The Authority has further directed the respondents to submit a detailed project completion report, along with a timeline of work and financial resources, within 30 days from the date of this order.

news.title: SC calls for IBC overhaul, seeks revival fund for stressed real estate projects
news.para: The Supreme Court proposed significant reforms to the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code to restore faith in the regulatory framework. It urged the government to establish a revival fund for stressed real estate projects and emphasized that housing is a fundamental right.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body to empanel third party agencies for fire safety audits
news.para: Chandigarh Municipal Corporation is set to empanel certified third-party agencies to conduct fire safety audits for over 25,000 buildings, addressing concerns about substandard equipment and preparedness. The move mandates BIS-certified installations, regular audits, and occupant training. Agencies will face penalties for violations, ensuring accountability and improved fire safety across the city.

news.title: Centurion REIT eyes $1.18 billion valuation, raising $771.1 million in Singapore IPO
news.para: Centurion Accommodation REIT is targeting a valuation of up to S$1.51 billion in its Singapore IPO, potentially becoming one of the largest listings this year. The company aims to raise S$771.1 million through the offering. Following the IPO, the REIT is poised to surpass NTT DC REIT's market capitalization, marking a significant milestone for Singapore's equities market.

news.title: SEBI reclassifies REITs as equity for mutual funds, widens strategic investor scope
news.para: SEBI has reclassified REITs as "equity" and retained InvITs under the "hybrid" category, amending mutual fund regulations to deepen participation. This decision, following public consultation and industry deliberations, aligns domestic practices with global standards, potentially increasing mutual fund allocation into REITs and fostering growth in the InvIT segment.

news.title: Court-monitored resolution process needed for Supertech Supernova project: Amicus to SC
news.para: The Supreme Court is considering a court-monitored resolution for Supertech's 'Supernova' project, similar to Amrapali and Unitech cases, potentially led by former Justice Navin Sinha. This proposal aims to protect homebuyers' interests amidst Supertech's insolvency, balancing the rights of financial creditors with the need to complete the project and deliver homes. A forensic audit and new management are also suggested.

news.title: DesignScape 2025: Industry leaders call for human-centric, sustainable and legacy-driven design
news.para: DesignScape 2025 commenced with Hafeez Contractor emphasizing the need for purpose-driven design, particularly in addressing India's housing challenges. Discussions revolved around balancing identity, sustainability, and functionality in architecture, with a focus on integrating local materials and artisanal skills. The event also explored the role of design in urban revitalization and recognized excellence in architecture and interior design.

news.title: Tarsadia Capital pushes Sunstone REIT to pursue a sale, or liquidate assets, letter says
news.para: Tarsadia Capital, holding 3.4% of Sunstone Hotel Investors' stock, is urging the REIT to explore a sale or liquidation due to its subscale size and underperformance. Citing a lack of investor appeal and vulnerability to market fluctuations, Tarsadia is also demanding board changes and threatens a proxy fight if its demands are unmet.

news.title: Goa land grab scam valuation likely to exceed ₹1,200 crore: ED
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) has uncovered a massive land grab scheme in Goa, allegedly orchestrated by Yeshwant Sawant and others, with the market value of the illegally acquired land exceeding Rs 1,200 crore. Searches across Goa and Hyderabad led to the seizure of Rs 72 lakh, luxury cars, and incriminating documents, revealing the mutation of over 3.
